<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse &uuml;lesanne </eesti>
<inglise>Purpose of Act </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolev seadus reguleerib kollektiivse t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li lahendamise ning streigi ja t&ouml;&ouml;sulu v&auml;ljakuulutamise ning korraldamise korda. </eesti>
<inglise>This Act regulates the procedures for the resolution of collective labour disputes and the calling and organisation of strikes and lock-outs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>M&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise>Definitions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kollektiivne t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li on lahkarvamus t&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andjate &uuml;hingu v&otilde;i liidu ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingu v&otilde;i liidu vahel, mis on tekkinud kollektiivlepingute s&otilde;lmimisel ja t&auml;itmisel ning uute t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste kehtestamisel. (20.12.95 j&otilde;ust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A collective labour dispute is a disagreement between an employer or an association or federation of employers and employees or a union or federation of employees which arises upon entry into or performance of collective agreements or establishment of new working conditions. </inglise>

<eesti>(2) Streik on t&ouml;&ouml;katkestus, mis toimub t&ouml;&ouml;tajate v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingu v&otilde;i liidu algatusel, saavutamaks t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andjate &uuml;hingult v&otilde;i liidult j&auml;releandmisi seaduslikes t&ouml;&ouml;alastes n&otilde;udmistes. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A strike is an interruption of work on the initiative of employees or a union or federation of employees in order to achieve concessions from an employer or an association or federation of employers to lawful demands in labour matters. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;sulg on t&ouml;&ouml;katkestus t&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andjate &uuml;hingu v&otilde;i liidu algatusel, saavutamaks t&ouml;&ouml;tajatelt v&otilde;i nende &uuml;hingult v&otilde;i liidult j&auml;releandmisi seaduslikes t&ouml;&ouml;alastes n&otilde;udmistes. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A lock-out is an interruption of work on the initiative of an employer or association or federation of employers in order to achieve concessions from employees or a union or federation of employees to lawful demands in labour matters. (20.12.95 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 3, 57) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Kollektiivse t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li pooled </eesti>
<inglise>Parties to collective labour dispute </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kollektiivse t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li poolteks on t&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andjate &uuml;hing v&otilde;i liit ning t&ouml;&ouml;tajad v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hing v&otilde;i liit. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The parties to a collective labour dispute are an employer or an association or federation of employers and employees or a union or federation of employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;tajaid, t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingut v&otilde;i liitu esindab nende poolt volitatud isik (edaspidi t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindaja). </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Employees or a union or federation of employees are represented by the person authorised by the employees or the union or federation of employees (hereinafter representative of employees). </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andjat, t&ouml;&ouml;andjate &uuml;hingut v&otilde;i liitu esindab nende poolt volitatud isik (edaspidi t&ouml;&ouml;andja). </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An employer or an association or federation of employers is represented by the person authorised by the employer or the association or federation of employers (hereinafter employer). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajate ja t&ouml;&ouml;andjate n&otilde;udmiste esitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Submission of demands of employees and employers </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajate ja t&ouml;&ouml;andjate n&otilde;udmised esitatakse teisele poolele kirjalikult. </eesti>
<inglise>Demands of employees and employers shall be submitted to the other party in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;udmiste l&auml;bivaatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Hearing of demands </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja, samuti t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindaja on kohustatud esitatud n&otilde;udmised l&auml;bi vaatama seitsme kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul nende esitamise p&auml;evast arvates ja teatama oma otsusest n&otilde;udmiste esitajale kirjalikult j&auml;rgmisel p&auml;eval p&auml;rast otsustamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employers and representatives of employees are required to hear submitted demands within seven calendar days after the date of their submission and to notify the persons who submitted the demands of their decision in writing on the date following the date of the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) N&otilde;udmiste l&auml;bivaatamise juurde v&otilde;ib kutsuda n&otilde;udmisi esitanud poole esindajaid ja v&auml;lja n&otilde;uda asja sisuliseks lahendamiseks vajalikke dokumente. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Representatives of the party which submitted demands may be invited to participate in the hearing of the demands, and may be required to submit documents necessary for the substantive resolution of the matter. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;list teatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Notice of labour dispute </inglise>
<eesti>Pooled p&ouml;&ouml;rduvad kirjalikult riikliku lepitaja poole, kui l&auml;bir&auml;&auml;kimiste k&auml;igus kokkulepet ei saavutata ning tekib t&ouml;&ouml;rahu katkemise oht. </eesti>
<inglise>The parties shall consult the Public Conciliator in writing if an agreement is not reached through negotiations and the threat of a disruption of work arises. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li lahendamine t&ouml;&ouml;andjate liidu ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate liidu poolt </eesti>
<inglise>Resolution of labour disputes by federations of employers and federations of employees </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;lide korral, mis k&auml;sitlevad t&ouml;&ouml;seaduste kohalda- mist, t&ouml;&ouml;andjate ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate v&otilde;i nende &uuml;hingute vaheliste kollektiivlepingute s&otilde;lmimist, t&auml;itmist ja muutmist, v&otilde;ivad t&ouml;&ouml;andja ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindaja omavahelise kokkuleppe mittesaavutamisel p&ouml;&ouml;rduda t&ouml;&ouml;andjate liidu ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate liidu poole. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Failing agreement on labour disputes which concern the application of labour legislation and entry into, performance or amendment of collective agreements between employers and employees or associations or unions thereof, the employers and representatives of the employees have the right of recourse to federations of employers and federations of employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andjate liit ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate liit moodustavad t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li lahendamiseks pariteetsel alusel komisjoni kolme p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates avalduse laekumisele j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast, millest teatatakse riiklikule lepitajale. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A federation of employers and a federation of employees shall, within three days after the date following receipt of an application, establish a committee on a basis of parity for resolution of a labour dispute and shall notify the Public Conciliator thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andjate liidu ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate liidu vahel saavutatud kokkulepe on vaidlevatele pooltele kohustuslik. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An agreement reached by a federation of employers and a federation of employees is binding on the parties to a dispute. </inglise>
<eesti>II peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter II </inglise>
<eesti>Lepitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Conciliation </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepitaja </eesti>
<inglise>Conciliator </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Lepitaja on erapooletu asjatundja, kes aitab t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li pooltel leida neid rahuldavat lahendust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Conciliators are impartial experts who help the parties to labour disputes reach mutually satisfactory resolutions. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Lepitaja on riiklik ja paikkondlik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Conciliators are the Public Conciliator or local conciliators. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepitaja p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruse kinnitab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The statutes of offices of conciliators are approved by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Riikliku lepitaja nimetab ametisse Vabariigi Valitsus Sotsiaalministeeriumi, t&ouml;&ouml;andjate ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate keskliitude &uuml;hise kokkuleppe alusel kolmeks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Public Conciliator is appointed to office for a term of three years by the Government of the Republic on the basis of a joint agreement of the Ministry of Social Affairs and central, federations of employers and federations of employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(02.06.98 j&otilde;ust. 06.07.98 - RT I 1998, 57, 858) </eesti>
<inglise>(02.06.98 entered into force 06.07.98 - RT I 1998, 57, 858) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Riiklik lepitaja m&auml;&auml;rab t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li lahendamiseks paikkondliku lepitaja, koosk&otilde;lastades selle eelnevalt kohaliku omavalitsusega, v&otilde;i v&otilde;tab t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li oma menetlusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Public Conciliator appoints a local conciliator for resolution of a labour dispute in prior co-ordination with the local government, or the Public Conciliator processes the dispute. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andjate liitude ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate liitude vahelisi t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;lisid lahendab riiklik lepitaja. </eesti>
<inglise>Labour disputes between federations of employers and federations of employees are resolved by the Public Conciliator. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Paikkondliku lepitaja vabastamisel oma &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmise ajaks p&otilde;hit&ouml;&ouml;st h&uuml;vitatakse talle saamata j&auml;&auml;nud t&ouml;&ouml;tasu seaduses etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon release of a local conciliator from the duties of his or her principal job for the period of performance of the duties of a conciliator, he or she is compensated for unreceived remuneration pursuant to procedure prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepitaja &uuml;lesanne </eesti>
<inglise>Duty of conciliator </inglise>
<eesti>Lepitaja &uuml;lesandeks on poolte lepitamine. </eesti>
<inglise>The duty of a conciliator is to effect conciliation of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepitaja selgitab v&auml;lja t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li p&otilde;hjused ja asjaolud ning pakub v&auml;lja lahendusi. </eesti>
<inglise>A conciliator shall identify the reasons for and circumstances of a labour dispute and shall propose resolutions. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepitaja &otilde;igused </eesti>
<inglise>Rights of conciliators </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Lepitajal on &otilde;igus kutsuda pooli osa v&otilde;tma lepitus- toimingutest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Conciliators have the right to invite the parties to participate in conciliation proceedings. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Lepitajal on &otilde;igus kaasata oma t&ouml;&ouml;sse asjatundjaid v&otilde;i eksperte ning p&auml;devaid ametiisikuid, kellele p&otilde;hit&ouml;&ouml;st vabastamise korral h&uuml;vitatakse saamata j&auml;&auml;nud t&ouml;&ouml;tasu seaduses etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Conciliators have the right to engage qualified persons or experts and competent officials in their work, who are compensated for unreceived remuneration pursuant to procedure prescribed by law upon their release from the duties of their principal jobs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Poolte lepitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Conciliation of parties </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Leppimine toimub lepitaja vahendusel v&otilde;i lepitaja omapoolse ettepaneku alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Conciliation is effected through the mediation of a conciliator or on the basis of a proposal made by a conciliator. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepitaja ettepanekule peavad pooled vastama kolme p&auml;eva jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>The parties shall reply to the proposal of a conciliator within three days. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Pooled on kohustatud osa v&otilde;tma lepitustoimingutest, saatma lepitustoimingutele oma t&auml;ievolilised esindajad ning esitama asja sisuliseks lahendamiseks vajalikud dokumendid lepitaja poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Parties are required to participate in conciliation proceedings, send their fully authorised representatives to participate in the conciliation proceedings and submit documents necessary for the substantive resolution of the matter by the date specified by the conciliator. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Leppimine vormistatakse protokolliga, millele kirjutavad alla poolte esindajad ja lepitaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Conciliation is documented by a report, which shall be signed by the representatives of the parties and the conciliator. </inglise>
<eesti>Protokoll koostatakse ka siis, kui kokkulepet ei saavutata. </eesti>
<inglise>A report shall also be prepared if no agreement is reached. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Allakirjutatud protokollis sisalduv leppimine on pooltele kohustuslik ja j&otilde;ustub allakirjutamise hetkest, kui ei ole kokku lepitud teises t&auml;htajas. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A conciliation contained in a signed report is binding on the parties and enters into force upon signature, unless a different date is agreed on. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Lepitaja ja t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li lahendamisest osav&otilde;tjad peavad hoidma neile lepitustoimingute k&auml;igus teatavaks saanud tootmis-, &auml;ri- v&otilde;i ametisaladusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A conciliator and the participants in the resolution of a labour dispute shall maintain any production, business or trade secrets which become known to them during the conciliation proceedings. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li lahendamine kohtus </eesti>
<inglise>Resolution of labour disputes in court </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;tajate ja t&ouml;&ouml;andjate liit kollektiivlepingu t&auml;itmisest tulenevas vaidluses kokkulepet ei saavuta, on neil &otilde;igus p&ouml;&ouml;rduda vaidluse lahendamiseks t&ouml;&ouml;vaidluskomisjoni v&otilde;i kohtusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Failing agreement between a federation of employers and a federation of employees in a dispute arising from the performance of a collective agreement, the federations have the right of recourse to labour dispute committees or the courts for resolution of the dispute. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Streigi ja t&ouml;&ouml;sulu korraldamine on keelatud, arvates t&ouml;&ouml;vaidluskomisjoni v&otilde;i kohtusse p&ouml;&ouml;rdumise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Organisation of strikes or lock-outs is prohibited as of the date of recourse to a labour dispute committee or court. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust. 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 3, 57) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 3, 57) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Streigi ja t&ouml;&ouml;sulu &otilde;iguse tekkimine </eesti>
<inglise>Creation of right to strike or lock out </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tajatel, t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingul v&otilde;i liidul tekib &otilde;igus korraldada t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li lahendamiseks streik, t&ouml;&ouml;andjal, t&ouml;&ouml;andjate &uuml;hingul v&otilde;i liidul aga t&ouml;&ouml;sulg &uuml;ksnes siis, kui t&ouml;&ouml;rahu kohustus ei kehti, kui k&auml;esolevas seaduses etten&auml;htud lepitusprotseduurid on t&auml;idetud, kuid leppimist ei ole saavutatud v&otilde;i ei peeta saavutatud kokkuleppest kinni v&otilde;i ei t&auml;ideta kohtuotsust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The right of employees or unions or federations of employees to organise a strike and the right of employers or associations or federations of employers to lock out employees to resolve a labour dispute arises only if there is no prohibition against disruption of work in force, if conciliation procedures prescribed in this Act have been conducted but no conciliation has been achieved, if an agreement is not complied with, or if a court order is not executed. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Streigi v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;sulu korral on pooled kohustatud taas alustama l&auml;bir&auml;&auml;kimisi kollektiivses t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;lis kokkuleppele j&otilde;udmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case of a strike or lock-out, the parties are required to resume negotiations in order to reach an agreement in the collective labour dispute. </inglise>
<eesti>III peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter III </inglise>
<eesti>Streik ja t&ouml;&ouml;sulg </eesti>
<inglise>Strikes and Lock-outs </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsuse tegemine </eesti>
<inglise>Decision-making </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Otsuse streigi korraldamise kohta teeb t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;ldkoosolek v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hing v&otilde;i liit. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A decision to organise a strike is made by a general meeting of employees or a union or federation of employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Otsuse t&ouml;&ouml;sulu korraldamise kohta teeb t&ouml;&ouml;andja. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A decision to organise a lock-out is made by an employer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Streigist v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;sulust etteteatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Advance notice of strike or lock-out </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kavandatavast streigist v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;sulust on streigi v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;sulu korraldaja kohustatud teatama teisele poolele, lepitajale ja kohalikule omavalitsusele kirjalikult v&auml;hemalt kaks n&auml;dalat ette. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Organisers of a strike or lock-out are required to notify the other party, a conciliator and the local government of a planned strike or lock-out in writing at least two weeks in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>Teates n&auml;idatakse streigi v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;sulu p&otilde;hjused, t&auml;pne algus ja v&otilde;imalik ulatus. </eesti>
<inglise>The notice shall set out the reasons, exact time of commencement and possible scope of the strike or lock-out. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Streigist v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;sulust on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud informeerima oma lepingupartnereid ning teisi huvitatud ettev&otilde;tteid ja asutusi, samuti massiteabevahendite kaudu &uuml;ldsust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employer is required to inform the parties with whom the employer has contracts, other interested enterprises or agencies and the public through the media of a strike or lock-out. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Streigi juhtimine </eesti>
<inglise>Direction of strike </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Streiki juhib streigi korraldamise otsuse teinud t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;ldkoosoleku v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingu v&otilde;i liidu poolt volitatud isik v&otilde;i isikud (streigijuht). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A strike is directed by a person or persons (strike leader) authorised by a general meeting of employees or a union or federation of employees which makes the decision to organise a strike. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Streigijuht tegutseb Eesti Vabariiki siduvate rahvusvaheliste &otilde;igusaktide, Eesti seaduste ja muude &otilde;igusaktide ning teda volitanud t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;ldkoosoleku v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingu v&otilde;i liidu otsustega etten&auml;htud &otilde;iguste piires, esindab teda volitanute huve streigi ajal ning informeerib massiteabevahendite kaudu &uuml;ldsust kollektiivse t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li lahendamise k&auml;igust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A strike leader shall act within the limits prescribed by international legislation binding on the Republic of Estonia, Acts and other legislation of Estonia and resolutions of the general meeting of employees or a union or federation of employees authorising the strike leader, shall represent the interests of those who authorised the strike leader during a strike and shall inform the public through the media about the course of resolution of the labour dispute. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud volitused l&otilde;pevad, kui pooled on alla kirjutanud leppimisele (kokkuleppele) kollektiivse t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li reguleerimise kohta, streigi ebaseaduslikuks tunnistamise korral kohtu poolt v&otilde;i streigijuhte volitanute otsuse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>Such authority terminates if the parties sign a conciliation (agreement) on the manner of regulation of the labour dispute, if the strike is declared unlawful by a court, or on the basis of a decision of the bodies authorising the strike leader. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Oma volituste t&auml;itmisel ei ole streigijuhil &otilde;igus vastu v&otilde;tta otsuseid, mis kuuluvad riigiorganite ja valitsusasutuste ja teiste organisatsioonide ning kollektiivse t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li teise poole p&auml;devusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the exercise of the authority of a strike leader, a strike leader does not have the right to adopt decisions which are within the competence of state bodies, government agencies or other organisations or the other party to the labour dispute. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Streigijuht on kohustatud rakendama meetmeid teise poole vara s&auml;ilimiseks, seaduslikkuse ja avaliku korra tagamiseks ning ta kannab vastutust streigiga kaasnenud &otilde;iguserikkumiste ja tekitatud kahjude eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A strike leader is required to apply measures to preserve the assets of the other party and to maintain the rule of law and public order, and is liable for violations of law and damage caused by a strike. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;sulu juhtimine </eesti>
<inglise>Direction of lock-out </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;sulgu juhitakse t&ouml;&ouml;andja poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>A lock-out is directed pursuant to the procedure determined by the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Hoiatus- ja toetusstreigid </eesti>
<inglise>Warning and support strikes </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tajatel, nende &uuml;hingutel v&otilde;i liitudel on &otilde;igus korraldada hoiatusstreike kestusega mitte &uuml;le &uuml;he tunni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employees and their unions or federations have the right to organise warning strikes with a duration of up to one hour. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Streigis osalevate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate toetuseks on lubatud korraldada toetusstreike. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Support strikes are permitted in support of employees engaging in a strike. </inglise>
<eesti>Streigi kestuse &uuml;le otsustab selle korraldamise kohta otsuse teinud t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindaja, &uuml;hing v&otilde;i liit. </eesti>
<inglise>The duration of such strikes shall be decided by the representative, union or federation of the employees who makes the decision to organise the strike. </inglise>
<eesti>Toetusstreik ei v&otilde;i kesta &uuml;le kolme p&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>A support strike shall not last longer than three days. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kavandatavast hoiatus- v&otilde;i toetusstreigist on t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindaja, &uuml;hing v&otilde;i liit kohustatud teatama t&ouml;&ouml;andjale, t&ouml;&ouml;andjate &uuml;hingule v&otilde;i liidule ja kohalikule omavalitsusele kirjalikult v&auml;hemalt kolm p&auml;eva ette. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A representative, union or federation of employees is required to notify the employer, association or federation of employers and the local government of a planned warning or support strike in writing at least three days in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Streigi ja t&ouml;&ouml;sulu edasil&uuml;kkamine v&otilde;i peatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Postponement or suspension of strike or lock-out </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Streigi v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;sulu algust v&otilde;ib edasi l&uuml;kata &uuml;ks kord: Vabariigi Valitsus riikliku lepitaja ettepanekul &uuml;he kuu v&otilde;i linna- v&otilde;i maakonnavalitsus paikkondliku lepitaja ettepanekul kahe n&auml;dala v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The commencement of a strike or lock-out may be postponed once: by one month by the Government of the Republic on the proposal of the Public Conciliator or by two weeks by the city or county government on the proposal of a local conciliator. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Loodus&otilde;nnetuse ja katastroofi korral v&otilde;i nakkushaiguse leviku t&otilde;kestamiseks, samuti erakorralise seisukorra ajal on Vabariigi Valitsusel &otilde;igus streik v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;sulg peatada. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Government of the Republic has the right to suspend a strike or lock-out in the case of a natural disaster or catastrophe, in order to prevent the spread of an infectious disease or in a state of emergency. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Streigist osav&otilde;tu vabadus </eesti>
<inglise>Freedom to participate in strike </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Streigist osav&otilde;tt on vabatahtlik. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Participation in a strike is voluntary. </inglise>
<eesti>Ei ole lubatud takistada streigiga mitte&uuml;hinenud t&ouml;&ouml;tajate t&ouml;&ouml;leasumist. </eesti>
<inglise>It is prohibited to impede the performance of work by employees who do not participate in a strike. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Keelatud on streigi &otilde;hutamine isikute poolt, kes ei t&ouml;&ouml;ta ettev&otilde;ttes, asutuses v&otilde;i muus organisatsioonis, kus t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li on tekkinud, v&otilde;i kes ei esinda t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid seadusega etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) It is prohibited for individuals who are not employed by an enterprise, agency or other organisation where a labour dispute arises or who do not represent the employees pursuant to procedure prescribed by law to instigate a strike. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Streigi korraldamise &otilde;iguse piiramine </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions on right to strike </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Streigid on keelatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Strikes are prohibited: </inglise>
<eesti>1) valitsusasutustes ja muudes riigiorganites ning kohalikes omavalitsustes; </eesti>
<inglise>1) in government agencies and other state bodies and local governments; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kaitsev&auml;es ja riigikaitseorganisatsioonides, kohtutes ning tulet&otilde;rje- ja p&auml;&auml;steteenistuses. </eesti>
<inglise>2) in the armed forces, other national defence organisations, courts, and fire fighting and rescue services. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud asutustes ja muudes organisatsioonides lahendatakse kollektiivsed t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;lid l&auml;bir&auml;&auml;kimiste teel riikliku lepitaja vahendusel v&otilde;i kohtus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Agencies and other organisations specified in subsection (1) of this section shall resolve collective labour disputes by negotiations, through the mediation of a conciliator or in court. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Elanike ja majanduse esmavajadusi rahuldavates ette v&otilde;tetes ja asutustes tagab streigi v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;sulu kuulutanud organ h&auml;davajaliku teenindus- v&otilde;i tootmismahu, mis m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks poolte omavahelise kokkuleppega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In enterprises and agencies which satisfy the primary needs of the population and economy, the body which calls a strike or locks out employees shall ensure indispensable services or production which shall be determined by agreement of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>Lahkarvamuste korral m&auml;&auml;rab h&auml;davajaliku teenindus- v&otilde;i tootmismahu riiklik lepitaja, kelle otsus on pooltele kohustuslik. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of disagreements, indispensable services or production shall be determined by the Public Conciliator whose decision is binding on the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Elanike ja majanduse esmavajadusi rahuldavate ettev&otilde;tete ja asutuste loetelu kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A list of enterprises and agencies which satisfy the primary needs of the population and economy shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Ebaseaduslikud streigid ja t&ouml;&ouml;sulud </eesti>
<inglise>Unlawful strikes and lock-outs </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Streik ja t&ouml;&ouml;sulg kohtu tegevuse m&otilde;jutamiseks on ebaseaduslikud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Strikes or lock-outs for the purpose of affecting the activities of courts are unlawful. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Streik ja t&ouml;&ouml;sulg, millele ei ole eelnenud l&auml;bir&auml;&auml;kimisi ja lepitustoiminguid, on ebaseaduslikud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Strikes or lock-outs which are not preceded by negotiations and conciliation proceedings are unlawful. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Streik ja t&ouml;&ouml;sulg, mille v&auml;ljakuulutamisel v&otilde;i korraldamisel on rikutud k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud korda v&otilde;i esitatakse n&otilde;udmisi, mis ei ole reguleeritud t&ouml;&ouml;seadustes v&otilde;i kollektiivlepingus, on ebaseaduslikud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Strikes or lock-outs which are called or organised in violation of the procedure established by this Act or in which demands are submitted which are unregulated by labour legislation or collective agreements are unlawful. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Streigi v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;sulu ebaseaduslikuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Declaration of strikes or lock-outs as unlawful </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Otsuse streigi v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;sulu ebaseaduslikuks tunnistamise kohta teeb kohus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A decision to declare a strike or lock-out unlawful is made by a court. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kohus teeb oma otsuse teatavaks t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li pooltele ja massiteabevahendite kaudu &uuml;ldsusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The court shall communicate its decision to the parties to the labour dispute and to the public through the media. </inglise>
<eesti>IV peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter IV </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;pps&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>Final Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Streigist osav&otilde;tjate ja t&ouml;&ouml;sulu korraldajate &otilde;igused ja vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Rights and liability of participants in strikes or lock-outs </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Seaduslikust streigist osav&otilde;ttu ei k&auml;sitleta t&ouml;&ouml;distsipliini rikkumisena ja see ei too kaasa distsiplinaarvastutust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Participation in a lawful strike shall not be considered to be a breach of work discipline and shall not result in disciplinary punishment. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isikud, kes organiseerivad v&otilde;i j&auml;tkavad ebaseaduslikuks tunnistatud v&otilde;i peatatud streiki v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;sulgu, samuti isikud, kes alustavad (j&auml;tkavad) edasil&uuml;katud streiki v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;sulgu m&auml;&auml;ratud ajast varem, kannavad vastutust seaduses etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Persons who organise or resume a strike or lock-out which has been declared unlawful or has been suspended and persons who commence (resume) a strike or lock-out which has been postponed, before the specified time, are held liable pursuant to procedure prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Streigi ajal on t&ouml;&ouml;andja algatusel t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine seaduslikus streigis osalejaga keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) It is prohibited to terminate the employment contracts of participants in lawful strikes on the initiative of an employer during a strike. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tasu streigi ja t&ouml;&ouml;sulu ajal </eesti>
<inglise>Remuneration during strike or lock-out </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Streigi v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;sulu aja eest t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele palka ei maksta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employees are not paid wages for the period of a strike or lock-out. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;tajale, kes streigist osa ei v&otilde;ta, kuid kes seet&otilde;ttu ei saa oma t&ouml;&ouml;d teha, maksab t&ouml;&ouml;andja tasu samadel alustel kui mitte t&ouml;&ouml;taja s&uuml;&uuml; t&otilde;ttu tekkinud t&ouml;&ouml;seisaku aja eest v&otilde;i kollektiivlepingus etten&auml;htud ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employee who does not participate in a strike but who cannot perform his or her work by reason of the strike shall be remunerated by the employer on the same bases as for the period of work stoppages which are not the fault of the employee or to the extent prescribed by a collective agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;taja, kes ei saanud t&ouml;&ouml;d teha ebaseaduslikuks tunnistatud t&ouml;&ouml;sulu t&otilde;ttu, loetakse t&ouml;&ouml;lt ebaseaduslikult k&otilde;rvaldatuks ja talle makstakse t&ouml;&ouml;sulu aja eest keskmist t&ouml;&ouml;tasu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An employee who cannot perform his or her work by reason of a lock-out which has been declared unlawful shall be deemed to be unlawfully suspended from work, and he or she shall be paid average wages for the period of the lock-out. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;tajate, t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingu v&otilde;i liidu n&otilde;uete t&auml;ieliku v&otilde;i osalise rahuldamise korral maksab t&ouml;&ouml;andja streigi v&auml;ljakuulutanud t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele, t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingule v&otilde;i liidule h&uuml;vitist poolte vahel kokkulepitavas suuruses. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon full or partial satisfaction of the demands of employees or a union or federation of employees, the employer shall pay compensation in an amount agreed upon by the parties to the employees or the union or federation of employees who called the strike. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutus ebaseaduslikuks tunnistatud streigi v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;sulu korral </eesti>
<inglise>Liability in case of strike or lock-out declared unlawful </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ebaseaduslikuks tunnistatud streigi korral kannavad streigi korraldajad vastutust seaduses etten&auml;htud korras ja ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a strike is declared unlawful, the organisers of the strike are held liable pursuant to procedure and to the extent prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ebaseaduslikuks tunnistatud t&ouml;&ouml;sulu korral kannab t&ouml;&ouml;sulu korraldaja vastutust seaduses etten&auml;htud korras ja ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a lock-out is declared unlawful, the organiser of the lock-out is held liable pursuant to procedure and to the extent prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>Kulude katmine </eesti>
<inglise>Covering of expenses </inglise>
<eesti>Kollektiivse t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li lahendamisega seotud kulud katab s&uuml;&uuml;diolev pool v&otilde;i need jaotatakse kokkuleppeliselt poolte vahel. </eesti>
<inglise>Expenses relating to the resolution of a collective labour dispute are covered by the party at fault or are divided between the parties by agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Streigi t&otilde;ttu kaotatud aja tasat&ouml;&ouml;tamine </eesti>
<inglise>Making up for time lost by reason of strike </inglise>
<eesti>Kollektiivse t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li poolte kokkuleppel v&otilde;ivad streigist osav&otilde;tnud streigi t&otilde;ttu kaotatud aja tasa t&ouml;&ouml;tada v&auml;ljaspool t&ouml;&ouml;aega. </eesti>
<inglise>By agreement of the parties to a labour dispute, participants in a strike may make up for the time lost by reason of a strike outside of working hours. </inglise>
<eesti>Streigi t&otilde;ttu kaotatud aja tasat&ouml;&ouml;tamist ei loeta &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;ks ega t&ouml;&ouml;ks puhkep&auml;evadel v&otilde;i riiklikel p&uuml;hadel. </eesti>
<inglise>Time spent making up for the time lost by reason of a strike shall not be deemed to be overtime or work on days off or public holidays. * RT = Riigi Teataja = State Gazette </inglise>


